# Blog — data digest rules

## Purpose

- **Value:** Publish **data in a post-shaped layout** that answers a question city pages are not designed to answer (e.g. A vs B), using **the same numbers** as our guides. Do **not** copy long narrative blocks from city pages; **synthesize, tabulate, and link** instead.
- **Not:** Generic “AI travel” copy, first-person travel stories, or anything that overclaims visa, tax, or school outcomes.

## URLs & registry

- Routes: `/blog` (index), `/blog/[slug]`.
- Register every post in `lib/blog/registry.ts` with `getAllBlogPosts()` / `BLOG_POSTS`.
- Each post: `listTitle` (H1, no brand), `title` (SERP, ends with ` | FamiRelo`, ≤ 70 characters total; target **~65–70** with keywords), `metaDescription` (≤ **165** characters, **one or two complete sentences** — write copy that already fits; `clipMetaDescription` is a last-resort trim with **no** `…`), `relatedCityIds` from `data/cities.json`, `publishedAt`, `tags`, `contentTypeLabel` (e.g. `Data digest`).

## SERP (align with `serp-metadata.mdc` and `serp-timeless.mdc`)

- Brand suffix: **`FamiRelo`**, not the full `Family Relocation Engine`, in the HTML `<title>` for blog.
- `buildPageMetadata` for canonical, OG, Twitter; **OG image** = first related city’s `resolveCityHeroImage` unless a post-specific asset is added later.
- `generateStaticParams` from `BLOG_POSTS`. Add new posts to `app/sitemap.ts` via the registry (already mapped).

## Layout & design

- **Layout:** `StickySearchHeader`, `Breadcrumb` (`Home` → `Blog` → current), `min-h-screen bg-[#F5EFE8]`, `max-w-3xl` article column — same family as country/city pages.
- **Readability:** Short paragraphs, real `<h2>` / `<h3>`, tables with `overflow-x-auto`, avoid walls of text.
- **Byline / framing:** “Data digest” (no dates in the title/subline unless the product owner asked). **No “last reviewed {month}” in SERP/OG** — see `serp-timeless.mdc`. The article body can say figures match the city guides, without a review month in the byline.
- **No “what this page is not” section in the middle** of a post — stay useful. One short scope line in the intro or a single FAQ is enough for legal/careful phrasing.
- **FAQ:** end with `BlogFaqSection` (accordion, same pattern as city guide FAQ) — not a flat `<dl>` list.
- **Footer block:** `You might also like` (or the same phrasing) with **internal** links to relevant city/country/destinations pages.
- **Premium:** Static digests are fine; the paid product can offer **interactivity, more dimensions, and saved comparisons** — do not make every blog post an app substitute. Point to the guides for depth.

## Structured data

- Use `lib/seo/buildBlogArticleJsonLd.ts`: `Article` + `BreadcrumbList` + optional `FAQPage` when the page shows matching Q&A.
- FAQs must be **on-page** and **aligned** with the FAQ schema; no FAQ stuffing that is not visible.

## New post checklist

- [ ] Add to `BLOG_POSTS` with all required fields
- [ ] Implement rendering in `app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx` (or a colocated content component) and `generateStaticParams` picks it up
- [ ] Title length / meta length spot-check
- [ ] `npm run build` — static generation must succeed
- [ ] Sitemap includes `/blog` and `/blog/slug` (registry-driven)
